mance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref name=\"SAG Awards 2018\">{{cite news|last1=Gonzalez|first1=Sandra|title=The full list of the 2018 SAG Awards nominees|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/12/13/entertainment/sag-awards-nominations/index.html|accessdate=24 January 2018|work=CNN|publisher=CNN|date=17 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2018 MTV Movie & TV Awards|2018]]\n| [[MTV Movie & TV Awards]]\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best On-Screen Duo|Best On-Screen Team]] <small>(with [[Gaten Matarazzo]], [[Finn Wolfhard]], [[Noah Schnapp]] and [[Sadie Sink]])</small>\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/mtv-movie-tv-awards-2018-nominations-complete-list-1108100 |title=MTV Movie & TV Awards: 'Black Panther,' 'Stranger Things' Top Nominations |last=Nordyke |first=Kimberly |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=May 3, 2018 |accessdate=May 3, 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180503235147/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/mtv-movie-tv-awards-2018-nominations-complete-list-1108100 |archivedate=May 3, 2018 }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2019 Kids' Choice Awards|2019]]\n|[[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]]\n|[[ Kids' Choice Award for Favorite Male TV Star|Favorite Male TV Star]]\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/kids-choice-awards-complete-list-nominees-2019-1190854|title=Kids' Choice Awards: 'Avengers: Infinity War' Tops Nominees; DJ Khaled to Host|last=Howard|first=Annie|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=February 26, 2019|accessdate=March 7, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2019 Teen Choice Awards|2019]]\n|[[Teen Choice Awards]]\n|[[Teen Choice Award for Choice Summer TV Star: Male|Choice Summer TV Actor]]\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Swift |first1=Andy |title=Teen Choice Awards: Stranger Things Leads Final Wave of 2019 Nominations |url=https://tvline.com/2019/07/08/teen-choice-awards-nominees-2019-stranger-things-full-list-nominations/ |website=TVLine |accessdate=19 July 2019 |language=en |date=8 July 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|5160895}}\n* {{IBDB name|493505}}\n\n{{ScreenActorsGuildAwards EnsembleTVDrama 2010\u20132019}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McLaughlin, Caleb}}\n[[Category:2001 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:African-American male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from New York City]]\n[[Category:American male child actors]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Caleb McLaughlin\n| image              = Caleb McLaughlin by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption            = McLaughlin at the 2017 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_name         = Caleb Reginald McLaughlin\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|2001|10|13}}\n| birth_place        = [[Carmel, New York|Carmel]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 2012\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Caleb Reginald McLaughlin'''<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Sean Hayes/Stranger Things Kids/Sheryl Crow|episode-link=|series=The Ellen DeGeneres Show|series-link=The Ellen DeGeneres Show|network=|date=25 October 2017|season=15|number=37}}</ref> (born October 13, 2001)<ref>{{cite web|title=The kids of \"Stranger Things\" wishing Caleb McLaughlin (Lucas) a happy birthday is pure #friendshipgoals|url=https://hellogiggles.com/reviews-coverage/tv-shows/kids-of-stranger-things-all-wished-caleb-mclaughlin-a-happy-birthday/|website=[[HelloGiggles]]|first=Sarah|last=Terry|date=October 13, 2016}}</ref> is an American actor and singer. He is known for playing Lucas Sinclair in the Netflix series ''[[Stranger Things]]''. McLaughlin began his career when he appeared in an opera called ''Lost in the Stars'' in [[Cooperstown, New York]] at the Glimmerglass Opera House.  He then played on the [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] stage as Young Simba in the musical ''[[The Lion King (musical)|The Lion King]]''. In 2017, McLaughlin appeared in the [[BET]] miniseries ''[[The New Edition Story]]'' as young Ricky Bell.\n\n==Early life==\nMcLaughlin grew up in [[Carmel, New York]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Caleb McLaughlin Biography, Celebrity Facts and Awards|url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/caleb-mclaughlin/bio/841502/|accessdate=August 24, 2015|website=[[TV Guide]]|date=August 20, 2015}}</ref> He attended Kent Primary School and later attended [[George Fischer Middle School]] for one year. He studied dance for a year at Happy Feet Dance School in Carmel under [[Chloe Matteson]] in New York and then at [[The Harlem School of the Arts]] under [[Aubrey Lynch]], former ''[[The Lion King (musical)|Lion King]]'' producer.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Silva|first1=Tiffany|title=CALEB MCLAUGHLIN IS HAVING A GREAT START TO 2017|url=https://bckonline.com/2017/01/10/caleb-mclaughlin-is-having-a-great-start-to-2017/|website=bckonline.com|accessdate=January 21, 2018|date=January 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Cabiles|first1=Janroe|title=Caleb McLaughlin: Stranger Stages|url=http://statusmagonline.com/features/caleb-mclaughlin-interview-july-2017/|website=statusmagonline.com|accessdate=January 21, 2018|date=July 7, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Noah Dreams of Origami Fortunes''\n| Noah\n| Short film<ref>{{cite web|last=Dunmore|first=Royce|title=Noah Dreams of Origami Fortunes (2012)|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2265704/|website=[[Internet Movie Database]]|accessdate=September 19, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n||2019\n| ''[[High Flying Bird]]''\n| Darius\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Concrete Cowboys (2020 film)|Concrete Cowboys]]''\n| Cole\n| Post-production\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\